body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Car Dealership Customer Service. My name is Eugene Brooks. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Donna Alexander.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Donna. To assist you better, can you please provide your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five, six seven eight, nine zero one two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you. Could you also share your email address with us?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, my email address is donna dot alexander at example dot com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for sharing that information, Donna. Is there anything specific you need assistance with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm feeling confused about my recent purchase and the warranty options.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand. Let's work together to clarify everything for you. Thank you for reaching out, Donna. We appreciate your time.
